 0.7000 on 15 July and a brief extension to 0.7021 on the 21st. That said, the daily candle from yesterday closed essentially flat at 0.6998, and today's session is tracking in similar fashion, suggesting the recovery momentum has stalled rather than reversed.\n\nThe structure story is one of compression near a key psychological and technical threshold. The 0.7000 area has acted as a gravitational centre over the past week, with the pair repeatedly testing above and retreating back beneath it. The prior reaction zone at 0.6959 \u2014 a level with four recorded touches \u2014 has provided a meaningful floor during the recovery phase, and the structure support at 0.6989 remains relevant as the more immediate cushion. To the topside, the 0.7184 prior reaction zone represents the next significant overhead reference, though the distance to that level underscores just how much work the bulls would need to do to shift the broader narrative materially. The recovery from late June's lows near the 0.6864 prior reaction zone was constructive, but the pair has yet to produce a convincing daily close that would suggest a sustained breakout above 0.7000 is underway.\n\nOn the hourly chart, the picture is one of gradual drift lower from yesterday's intraday high of 0.7027. The H1 sequence from the early hours of Tuesday's Asian session through to the current European afternoon shows a gentle but persistent fade, with each attempted bounce capped in the 0.7008\u20130.7013 area. Price is now consolidating in a narrow band between roughly 0.6997 and 0.7006, with no meaningful directional conviction evident. The 0.6997\u20130.7000 zone is acting as near-term intraday support; a sustained hourly close below that area would open the path back toward the 0.6989 structure support on the daily.\n\nThe economic calendar carries no scheduled releases of note today, which removes a clear catalyst for a directional break in either direction. In the absence of data-driven volatility, price action is likely to remain technically driven and range-bound, with liquidity conditions potentially thinning into the latter part of the session.\n\nThe bullish read would require a clean daily close above 0.7010\u20130.7020 on meaningful volume, reaffirming the recovery from June's lows. Conversely, a daily close back beneath the 0.6959 prior reaction zone would materially weaken the constructive case and bring the 0.6864 area back into focus as a structural reference. For now, the desk reads this as a neutral consolidation at a pivotal level.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}